wikipedia_page.main: George Edward Hollest (born 28 November 1793 in Frimley, Surrey; died 29 September 1850 in Frimley) was an English first-class cricketer associated with Cambridge University who was active in the 1820s. He is recorded in one match in 1821, totalling 1 run with a highest score of 1.Hollest was educated at Winchester and Emmanuel College, Cambridge. After Cambridge he became a Church of England priest and was priest in charge of Frimley parish from 1832 until his death.
